%I A395587 #48 Jun 24 2026 19:52:49
%S A395587 7,271,1999,85751,1329668999
%N A395587 Smallest prime p such that p^(q^2) = +-1 mod q^5 is true when q is any of the first n primes.
%H A395587 Rhys Feltman, <a href="/A395587/a395587.txt">Python code</a>
%e A395587 a(1) = 7 because 7^(2^2) mod 2^5 = +-1: 7^4 = 2401, which equals 32*75 + 1. 5^(2^2) mod 2^5 does not work. 5^4 = 625, which is 32*20 - 15. 3^(2^2) does not work either, as 3^4 = 81 is 32*3 - 15, and 2 obviously does not work because 2^m mod 2^n will always be either 0 or 2^m.
%o A395587 (PARI) isok(p, vp) = for (i=1, #vp, my(q=vp[i], q5=q^5, m=Mod(p, q5)^q^2); if ((m != Mod(1, q5)) && (m != Mod(-1, q5)), return(0));); 1;
%o A395587 a(n) = my(p=2, vp=primes(n)); while (!isok(p, vp), p=nextprime(p+1)); p; \\ _Michel Marcus_, Jun 13 2026
%Y A395587 Cf. A396786 (with q^3 instead of q^2).
%K A395587 nonn,more,new
%O A395587 1,1
%A A395587 _Rhys Feltman_, Jun 05 2026
%E A395587 a(5) from _Michel Marcus_, Jun 13 2026
